cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for 3D pose estimation from 2D skeletal joints. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a lifting network and camera viewpoints indicates that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper involves the use of a discriminator, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves geometric self-consistency, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics).
